import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['cx'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['cx'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['cx'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['cx'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Longitude Coordinates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude coordinates of the London borough centroids?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['cy'], bins=10, color='green', alpha=0.8)
    plt.axvline(data['cy'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['cy'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Latitude Coordinates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.bar(data['name'], data['cx'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['cx'].max(), color='r', linestyle='-',
                label=f"Max Longitude: {data['cx'].max():.2f}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("Which borough has the highest longitude coordinate?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
